tching amp_mult for normalized phrase position x<br/>- defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, peak=0.6, k=1.0<br/>- arc_shape parameter supports parabolic, cosine, asymmetric-Bezier, flat, inverted variants<br/>- composes multiplicatively with SectionEnvelope.tempo_base at each event<br/>- tests verify arc shape, peak position, and multiplicative composition |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 5 | T-005 | Implement R3 Agogic Accent: lengthen + emphasize notes at local contour apex or harmonic-charge peak. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-014 | — | - `render/rules/agogic.py` detects contour apex (up-down peak) and harmonic_charge peak per phrase<br/>- at apex: duration multiplied by 1.05–1.15, velocity +3–6 dB<br/>- only one apex accent per phrase to avoid caricature<br/>- tests verify apex detection, magnitude, and one-per-phrase rule |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 6 | T-006 | Implement R4 Duration Contrast: exaggerate short-vs-long by log(dur_ratio_to_median), melodic roles only, capped at ±10%. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-015 | — | - `render/rules/duration_contrast.py` applies log-scaled multiplier within [0.90, 1.10] on melodic voices<br/>- ostinato / perc skipped<br/>- tests verify short notes shortened, long notes lengthened, and cap enforcement |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 7 | T-007 | Implement R5 Final Ritardando: Friberg–Sundberg square-root tempo curve over last 20–30% of cadential phrases. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-016 | — | - `render/rules/final_rit.py` applies tempo(x) = v₀·√(1 - α·(x-x_start)/(x_end-x_start)) for cadential phrases only<br/>- α default 0.35, onset position default 0.75 of phrase length<br/>- triggered only when is_cadential=True on phrase<br/>- tests verify curve shape, onset position, and non-application on non-cadential phrases |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 8 | T-008 | Implement R6 Punctuation + Breath: lengthen terminal note at phrase boundary and insert breath silence of breath_after_ms. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-017 | — | - `render/rules/punctuation.py` multiplies terminal-note duration by 1.15–1.40 and inserts breath drawn from Gauss(breath_after_ms, 0.1·breath_after_ms)<br/>- breath counts against R10 silence budget<br/>- tests verify terminal-note extension, breath insertion, and budget accounting |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 9 | T-009 | Implement R7 Articulation Shaping: per-note gate-time by style (legato 0.95–1.02, normal 0.7–0.85, staccato 0.3–0.5, staccatissimo 0.15–0.25) with contour adjustments. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-018 | — | - `render/rules/articulation.py` sets dur_sec as gate_time × nominal<br/>- repeated-pitch notes slightly shorter (×0.92); notes after upward leaps slightly longer (×1.05)<br/>- tests verify gate-time range per style and contour adjustments |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 10 | T-010 | Implement R8 Microtiming Polish: per-note Gaussian jitter σ=3 ms on melodic, 1 ms on ostinato, 0 ms on grid-locked machine voices. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-019 | — | - `render/rules/microtiming.py` is the ONLY place white noise enters the pipeline<br/>- σ values below listener JND (10 ms) by design<br/>- grid-locked voices receive σ=0 and emerge with timing_deviation_ms==0<br/>- tests verify σ by role and zero-jitter on grid-locked |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 1 | T-001 | Implement buffer-management protocol: `OnSamplerLoad(record)` allocates scsynth buffer + reads WAV; `OnSamplerFree` releases buffer; LRU eviction at 64-buffer cap. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-010 | — | - `tools/senseweave/sampler_buffers.py` exposes `BufferPool(scsynth_client, capacity=64)` with `acquire(record) -> bufnum`, `release(record)`, `evict_lru()`<br/>- WAV file path → `/b_allocRead bufnum path 0 -1` over OSC<br/>- LRU eviction triggered automatically when `acquire` exceeds capacity<br/>- on scsynth restart, pool detects buffer-id reuse failure and rebuilds<br/>- tests with a mock OSC client verify allocate, evict, release, and reuse paths |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 2 | T-002 | Implement `sampler_effects.scd` dedicated effects-bus SynthDef chain: long delay (1/4 to 1/2 measure), convolution reverb (FreeVerb fallback if no IR loaded), spec