12 100644\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n--- a/sdp/implementation-plan.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+++ b/sdp/implementation-plan.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -1,9 +1,9 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-# PRD: CypherClaw Humanization — Structured Expression Rendering Layer — Implementation Plan\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# PRD: CypherClaw Sampler — Granular Memory Voice as Primary Instrument — Implementation Plan\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Generated:** 2026-04-16T18:19:25.335643+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Generated:** 2026-04-25T18:39:59.551260+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n **Source:** PRD v1.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Total tasks:** 40\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Estimated effort:** ~129 hours\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Total tasks:** 33\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Estimated effort:** ~111 hours\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -15,16 +15,16 @@ Sprints are sequential. Tasks within a sprint can run in parallel unless a depen\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n **Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-001** [T1] Build a rule-ablation debugger that re-renders a score with selected rules disabled to localize expressive problems. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-002** [T1] Build the RenderPass framework: ordered rule stack with stable order, per-rule enable flags, per-rule quantity k, and role-filter gating. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-003** [T1] Implement R1 Metric Accent: per-beat-position velocity multiplier applied only to non-grid-locked melodic/accent voices. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-004** [T1] Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-005** [T1] Implement R3 Agogic Accent: lengthen + emphasize notes at local contour apex or harmonic-charge peak. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-006** [T1] Implement R4 Duration Contrast: exaggerate short-vs-long by log(dur_ratio_to_median), melodic roles only, capped at ±10%. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-007** [T1] Implement R5 Final Ritardando: Friberg–Sundberg square-root tempo curve over last 20–30% of cadential phrases. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-008** [T1] Implement R6 Punctuation + Breath: lengthen terminal note at phrase boundary and insert breath silence of breath_after_ms. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-009** [T1] Implement R7 Articulation Shaping: per-note gate-time by style (legato 0.95–1.02, normal 0.7–0.85, staccato 0.3–0.5, staccatissimo 0.15–0.25) with contour adjustments. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-010** [T1] Implement R8 Microtiming Polish: per-note Gaussian jitter σ=3 ms on melodic, 1 ms on ostinato, 0 ms on grid-locked machine voices. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-001** [T1] Implement buffer-management protocol: `OnSamplerLoad(record)` allocates scsynth buffer + reads WAV; `OnSamplerFree` releases buffer; LRU eviction at 64-buffer cap. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-002** [T1] Implement `sampler_effects.scd` dedicated effects-bus SynthDef chain: long delay (1/4 to 1/2 measure), convolution reverb (FreeVerb fallback if no IR loaded), spectral freeze (PV_Freeze), comb-resonance tuned to B fundamental (61.74 Hz). (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-003** [T1] Implement `sampler_dispatch.py` that converts a `(SampleRecord, PerformanceIntent, params)` tuple into the OSC bundle (`/s_new sw_sampler ...` + buffer-pool acquire) and ships it to scsynth. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-004** [T1] Per-voice gate-controlled lifecycle: composer can `play_sampler(record, duration_sec)` for fire-and-forget OR `start_sampler(record) -> handle; stop_sampler(handle)` for sustained voices. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-005** [T1] Integrate sampler effects bus into `master_bus.py` mix slot with appropriate gain staging (peak-normalized, not RMS) and post-mix compression bypass to preserve grain transients. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-006** [T1] Implement `sample_capture_daemon.py` rolling 60-second buffers reading from `system:capture_1` (contact mic) and `system:capture_2` (room mic) via JACK. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-007** [T1] Implement interesting-moment detector: novelty (spectral flux) + transient density + RMS thresholds + duration-min/max gating. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-008** [T1] Auto-tag captured samples: arc phase, mood, presence, time-of-day, plus heuristic acoustic tags (warm if low spectral centroid, metallic if high+narrow band, transient if high transient density, etc.). (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-009** [T1] Captured samples land in `samples/contact/` or `samples/room/` as 24-bit 48 kHz WAV with metadata-tagged filename and an entry in `index.sqlite`. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-010** [T1] Implement self-quotation loop: when a song completes with arc-payoff > threshold AND clicks=0, sample a 4-second window of `SuperCollider:out_1` for the next session. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n *Subtotal: ~30 hours*\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -32,47 +32,42 @@ Sprints are sequential. Tasks within a sprint can run in parallel unless a depen\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n **Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System), Sprint 1 (Quality Scoring)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-011** [T1] Implement R12 Sensor-to-Intent Aggregation Matrix: smoothed IIR + hysteresis → aggregate intentions (global_energy, global_restraint, global_brightness). (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-012** [T1] Implement bounded reactive delta track in scheduler with per-parameter modulation caps. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-013** [T1] Expose aggregate-intention telemetry (global_energy/restraint/brightness) in operator diagnostics, never raw one-to-one mappings. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-014** [T1] Build the metric battery: IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR/DNODR, pitch-class entropy H1, Grooving Similarity (GS), tempo autocorrelation ρ₁, LZ76 compression ratio, novelty peaks per phrase, silence-at-phrase-boundaries. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-015** [T1] Build anti-pattern tests: quantization ghosting, dynamic compression, motif ossification, random-as-expression (Ljung-Box), symmetric-arc uncanny, dead-silence failure. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-016** [T1] Implement performance-worm logger: 2D trajectory in tempo–loudness space + convex-hull area computation as CI artifact. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-017** [T1] Integrate metric battery + anti-pattern detectors into CI gate with fail-on-regression policy. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-018** [T1] Embed rule-stack provenance in exported audio metadata (e.g., WAV iXML chunk or sidecar JSON) for listener-review workflow. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-011** [T1] Implement anti-pattern detectors: `sampler_dominating` (sampler event count > 0.6 × total events) and `sampler_silent_quintet_member` (sampler used in <5% of last 50 pieces, mode-weighted). (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-012** [T1] End-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw: capture a known room sound, watch the composer self-quote it within 3 pieces, verify the self-listener observes the resulting peaks. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-013** [T2] Update `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to reflect the quintet, document the sampler architecture in `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md`, and add a one-page artistic-intent doc `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-artistic-intent.md`. (~6h) → deps: T-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-*Subtotal: ~24 hours*\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+*Subtotal: ~12 hours*\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ### Sprint 3: Improvement Engine Hardening\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n **Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System), Sprint 2 (Improvement Engine Hardening)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-019** [T1] Enforce role-filter gating across R1–R8 with a single shared contract; verify machine identity preservation end-to-end. (~3h) → deps: T-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-020** [T1] Integrate partitura for phrase-feature extraction: harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, cadential detection, contour apex. (~3h) → deps: T-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-021** [T1] Implement R9 Motif Memory: LRU cache of motif hashes with variation menu and return-home decay. (~3h) → deps: T-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-022** [T1] Implement R10 Silence Budget: per-voice and per-section accumulators enforced at phrase boundaries. (~3h) → deps: T-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-023** [T1] Implement wind/voice lung-capacity constraints: 4–8 s continuous-play cap per instrument-sim voice. (~3h) → deps: T-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-024** [T1] Implement R11 Call-Response Gating: follower phrase intent complements leader's realized performance. (~3h) → deps: T-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-025** [T1] Compose SectionEnvelope with phrase arcs multiplicatively so section-level tempo elasticity modulates phrase-level shaping. (~3h) → deps: T-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-026** [T1] Implement tempo-dependent swing curve per Friberg/Sundström (3.5:1 at slow tempi down toward 1:1 at fast), with short-note near-constant ~100 ms. (~3h) → deps: T-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-027** [T1] Add arc-shape variety so not every phrase uses a symmetric parabola: per-phrase random selection from parabolic/cosine/asymmetric-Bezier/flat/inverted with peak-position variance. (~3h) → deps: T-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-028** [T1] Implement restraint parameter enforced as global dampener across rules. (~3h) → deps: T-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-014** [T2] Add systemd unit `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` that runs `sample_capture_daemon.py` with `Restart=always`, dependent on `cypherclaw-jack.service`. (~6h) → deps: T-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-015** [T1] Implement TDD-grade test fixtures with canned 1-second audio windows representing each detector branch (silence, footsteps, dishwasher, music, dogs, transient cluster) for fast deterministic CI. (~3h) → deps: T-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-016** [T1] Wire `SampleSelector` into `cast_planner.select_cast_ids` so when the cast includes `sw_sampler`, a sample is pre-selected for the piece and attached to the cast metadata. (~3h) → deps: T-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-017** [T1] Per-mode sampler density gates: composer plays `floor(sampler_density * total_phrases) + Bernoulli(sampler_density)` sampler events per piece (clamped 0..total). (~3h) → deps: T-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-018** [T1] When a human plays the MIDI keyboard or Theramini for >5 seconds during a song, capture that input phrase to `samples/keyboard/` or `samples/theramini/` with full tagging. (~3h) → deps: T-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-019** [T1] Sample-aware harmonic planning: when a sample with known `pitch_hz` is selected, transpose to fit t