ity range < 20 → fail<br/>- motif ossification: GS > 0.95 across repeated sections → fail<br/>- random-as-expression: Ljung-Box fails to reject white noise on tempo or velocity series → fail<br/>- symmetric-arc uncanny: per-phrase worm convex-hull shape variance < 5% across phrases → fail<br/>- dead-silence failure: no rests ≥200 ms in a 2-minute melodic passage → fail<br/>- each detector has a positive fixture (should fail) and negative fixture (should pass) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 16 | T-016 | Implement performance-worm logger: 2D trajectory in tempo–loudness space + convex-hull area computation as CI artifact. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-036 | T-001 | - `render/worm.py` emits per-piece worm JSON and PNG to `artifacts/worms/<piece_id>/`<br/>- convex-hull area computed via scipy.spatial.ConvexHull<br/>- reject point-worm (mechanical: area < 1.0) and space-filling worm (random: area > saturation threshold)<br/>- CI attaches worm PNGs to build artifacts for listener review |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 17 | T-017 | Integrate metric battery + anti-pattern detectors into CI gate with fail-on-regression policy. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-037 | T-001 | - pytest gate runs metrics on a curated fixture set of 5-minute rendered pieces<br/>- any metric outside pass band or any anti-pattern trigger fails the build<br/>- pass bands are per-intent-tag where applicable (withhold-tagged phrases allow lower velocity σ)<br/>- tests verify a deliberately broken render fails the gate and a healthy render passes |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 18 | T-018 | Embed rule-stack provenance in exported audio metadata (e.g., WAV iXML chunk or sidecar JSON) for listener-review workflow. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-039 | T-001 | - each rendered audio file gets a `.render.json` sidecar with Event list, rule_stack per event, PerformanceIntent per phrase, SectionEnvelope per section, seeds, delta_track path<br/>- format documented in `my-claw/docs/render-audio-sidecar.md`<br/>- tests verify sidecar 