\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Agent selector — rotates agents using fitness-based selection with alternation penalties.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3086:PROVIDERS = {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3104:# Default fitness seeds per agent per category\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3117:    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Selects the best agent for a task based on fitness scores + rotation.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3123:        self._last_lead_provider = None\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3132:                self._last_lead_provider = data.get(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"last_lead_provider\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3143:                    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"last_lead_provider\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": self._last_lead_provider,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3156:    def get_fitness(self, agent: str, category: str) -> float:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3157:        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Get fitness score for agent+category from Observatory or defaults.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3413:**Depends on:** `prd-model-awareness.md` (model registry, model selector, per-model fitness scoring — currently being implemented by sdp-cli on server)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3482:| GW-007 | Create `tools/art_experimenter.py` implementing the scientific calibration framework. The experimenter maintains a grid of configurations to test: (model × effort × temperature × art_type × dimensions × theme_category). During the 3-day calibration period, it systematically works through this grid, running each configuration at least 3 times for statistical significance. It tracks: success_rate (valid art produced), avg_composite_score, score_variance, generation_time, retry_count. After calibration, it produces a ranked leaderboard of model configurations and recommends the optimal config for each art_type. The experimenter should also detect when models change (e.g., provider updates) and trigger re-calibration for affected configurations. | MUST | T3 | - Experiment grid covers all available models from model registry<br/>- Each config tested minimum 3 times during calibration<br/>- Statistics computed: mean, variance, success rate per config<br/>- Leaderboard ranked by composite score<br/>- Recommended configs exported as JSON<br/>- Re-calibration triggered when model registry changes<br/>- Progress trackable (X/Y configs tested) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3490:| GW-015 | Integrate with the model registry from the model-awareness PRD. The art experimenter (GW-007) should pull available models from `tools/model_registry.py` (being built by the model-awareness pipeline). When the model registry adds or removes models, the experimenter detects the change and queues new calibration runs for the changed models. Art generation calls should use `run_agent()` with the model parameter (REQ-004 from model-awareness PRD) to invoke specific model+effort combinations. Fitness scores from art generation should feed back into the Observatory's per-model tracking (REQ-007, REQ-008). | MUST | T2 | - Art engine reads available models from model_registry<br/>- Model changes detected and trigger re-calibration<br/>- run_agent() used with model parameter for generation<br/>- Art scores recorded in Observatory per-model tracking<br/>- Art-specific fitness scores (composite, per-criterion) tracked separately from code task fitness |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3724:**Depends on:** `prd-model-awareness.md` (model registry, model selector, per-model fitness scoring — currently being implemented by sdp-cli on server)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3793:| GW-007 | Create `tools/art_experimenter.py` implementing the scientific calibration framework. The experimenter maintains a grid of configurations to test: (model × effort × temperature × art_type × dimensions × theme_category). During the 3-day calibration period, it systematically works through this grid, running each configuration at least 3 times for statistical significance. It tracks: success_rate (valid art produced), avg_composite_score, score_variance, generation_time, retry_count. After calibration, it produces a ranked leaderboard of model configurations and recommends the optimal config for each art_type. The experimenter should also detect when models change (e.g., provider updates) and trigger re-calibration for affected configurations. | MUST | T3 | - Experiment grid covers all available models from model registry<br/>- Each config tested minimum 3 times during calibration<br/>- Statistics computed: mean, variance, success rate per config<br/>- Leaderboard ranked by composite score<br/>- Recommended configs exported as JSON<br/>- Re-calibration triggered when model registry changes<br/>- Progress trackable (X/Y configs tested) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3801:| GW-015 | Integrate with the model registry from the model-awareness PRD. The art experimenter (GW-007) should pull available models from `tools/model_registry.py` (being built by the model-awareness pipeline). When the model registry adds or removes models, the experimenter detects the change and queues new calibration runs for the changed models. Art generation calls should use `run_agent()` with the model parameter (REQ-004 from model-awareness PRD) to invoke specific model+effort combinations. Fitness scores from art generation should feed back into the Observatory's per-model tracking (REQ-007, REQ-008). | MUST | T2 | - Art engine reads available models from model_registry<br/>- Model changes detected and trigger re-calibration<br/>- run_agent() used with model parameter for generation<br/>- Art scores recorded in Observatory per-model tracking<br/>- Art-specific fitness scores (composite, per-criterion) tracked separately from code task fitness |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:4040:**Depends on:** `prd-model-awareness.md` (model registry, model selector, per-model fitness scoring — currently being implemented by sdp-cli on server)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:4109:| GW-007 | Create `tools/art_experimenter.py` implementing the scientific calibration framework. The experimenter maintains a grid of configurations to test: (model × effort × temperature × art_type × dimensions × theme_category). During the 3-day calibration period, it systematically works through this grid, running each configuration at least 3 times for statistical significance. It tracks: success_rate (valid art produced), avg_composite_score, score_variance, generation_time, retry_count. After calibration, it produces a ranked leaderboard of model configurations and recommends the optimal config for each art_type. The experimenter should also detect when models change (e.g., provider updates) and trigger re-calibration for affected configurations. | MUST | T3 | - Experiment grid covers all available models from model registry<br/>- Each config tested minimum 3 times during calibration<br/>- Statistics computed: mean, variance, success rate per config<br/>- Leaderboard ranked by composite score<br/>- Recommended configs exported as JSON<br/>- Re-calibration triggered when model registry changes<br/>- Progress trackable (X/Y configs tested) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:4117:| GW-015 | Integrate with the model registry from the model-awareness PRD. The art experimenter (GW-007) should pull available models from `tools/model_registry.py` (being built by the model-awareness pipeline). When the model registry adds or removes models, the experimenter detects the change and queues new calibration runs for the changed models. Art generation calls should use `run_agent()` with the model parameter (REQ-004 from model-awareness PRD) to invoke specific model+effort combinations. Fitness scores from art generation should feed back into the Observatory's per-model tracking (REQ-007, REQ-008). | MUST | T2 | - Art engine reads available models from model_registry<br/>- Model changes detected and trigger re-calibration<br/>- run_agent() used with model parameter for generation<br/>- Art scores recorded in Observatory per-model tracking<br/>- Art-specific fitness scores (composite, per-criterion) tracked separately from code task fitness |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:4228:/home/user/cypherclaw/tools/.agent_selector_state.json\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_context_pulse_runtime.py:29:    selector_state = tools_dir / \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".agent_selector_state.json\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_context_pulse_runtime.py:30:    selector_state.write_text(json.dumps({\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"last_lead\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"codex\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"last_lead_provider\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"openai\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_count\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 9}))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/startup-wizard.md:79:- CypherClaw live command projects can layer quota-aware routing on top of those rules, redistributing work away from providers with degraded headroom and collapsing to single-agent mode when only one provider remains viable.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/startup-wizard.md:87:- In live CypherClaw homes, operator roadmap/status commands are also queue-backed where possible, so Telegram `/monitor`, `/prd`, and `/tasks` reflect the actual queue state and implementation order from `.sdp/state.db` instead of stale narrative summaries. Their totals count live executable tasks and exclude only split parents. `/monitor` also keeps `needs split` separate from `pending`, exposes queue-state drift if active task records and open run records disagree, and now includes compact `sdp-cli`-style gate/recent/provider lines. `/prd` distinguishes between stages that are truly absent, stages that are frozen, and stages that have only split-parent/decomposed work. `/tasks` defaults to the next actionable queue slices and supports focused backlog views like `/tasks pending 10`, `/tasks frozen`, `/tasks prd 6`, and `/tasks stage clone and home creation`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:12:import agent_selector\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:42:    def get_provider_status(self) -> dict[str, dict[str, object]]:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:44:        for agent_name, provider in agent_selector.PROVIDERS.items():\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:45:            result[provider] = {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:46:                \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": self.statuses.get(provider, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"healthy\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:57:    def test_select_excludes_paused_provider(self, monkeypatch: pytest.MonkeyPatch, tmp_path: Path) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:58:        selector = agent_selector.AgentSelector(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:63:        monkeypatch.setattr(agent_selector.random, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"random\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", lambda: 1.0)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:68:        selector = agent_selector.AgentSelector(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:77:        monkeypatch.setattr(agent_selector.random, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"random\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", lambda: 1.0)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:86:        selector = agent_selector.AgentSelector(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:91:        monkeypatch.setattr(agent_selector.random, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"random\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", lambda: 1.0)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:96:        selector = agent_selector.AgentSelector(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:104:        monkeypatch.setattr(agent_selector.random, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"random\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", lambda: 1.0)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:105:        monkeypatch.setattr(selector, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"get_fitness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", lambda agent_name, category: 0.50)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:110:        selector = agent_selector.AgentSelector(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:115:        monkeypatch.setattr(agent_selector.random, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"random\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", lambda: 1.0)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:120:        selector = agent_selector.AgentSelector(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:184:  - `/home/user/cypherclaw/tools/agent_selector.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:262:- `grep -r \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"anthropic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\|openai\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\|gemini\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\|claude\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" /home/user/cypherclaw/tools/ --include=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"*.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" -l` showed provider-aware code in:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:268:  - `/home/user/cypherclaw/tools/agent_selector.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:275:  - `agent_selector = AgentSelector(observatory=observatory, state_file=...)`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:338:  - `/home/user/cypherclaw/tools/agent_selector.py` (`6.9K`)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/coherence-foundations.md:184:When a system uses multiple LLM providers (Claude, GPT, Gemini, local models), each with different capabilities and failure modes, governance rules cannot be embedded in any single model's system prompt. They must be externalized into infrastructure that evaluates all models' outputs uniformly. PromptClaw's constitution is model-agnostic: it evaluates text output regardless of which agent or model produced it.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/command-reference.md:90:In CypherClaw live command deployments, `run` can also honor `sdp-cli` quota telemetry. Healthy and warn providers stay eligible for routing, degraded providers stop receiving new work, and full exhaustion falls back to the provider with the best remaining headroom so runs continue in degraded mode.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/command-reference.md:174:- `/quota` shows provider headroom, active agents, and exclusions from quota-aware routing.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:218:### 2.1 Modify agent_selector.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:220:Add Ollama to the provider map and fitness scores:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:223:# In agent_selector.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:225:PROVIDERS = {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:257:# In quota_monitor.py, in _load_provider_headroom() or get_agent_headroom()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:260:    provider = PROVIDERS.get(agent)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:261:    if provider == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"local\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:286:    category = agent_selector.detect_category(task_label or prompt[:200])\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:734:Once you've validated that Ollama produces acceptable results, increase its fitness scores to make it the default choice:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:737:# In agent_selector.py, raise ollama scores above cloud agents:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:771:If Ollama is down, the agent selector naturally falls back to cloud agents (they have the next-highest fitness scores and full quota).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:800:| 4 | Apply code changes (agent_selector, daemon, quota_monitor) | Day 10 | Step 3 |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:805:| 9 | Monitor, tune fitness scores | Day 11+ | Production traffic |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/architecture.md:54:- when a live provider should be deprioritized or excluded because quota headroom is degraded\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/architecture.md:87:In CypherClaw-style live command deployments, command routing can consult `sdp-cli` quota telemetry. Healthy and warn providers remain eligible, degraded and paused providers are excluded from new work, and if every provider is degraded the runtime falls back to the provider with the most remaining headroom instead of refusing to operate.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++docs/architecture.md:115:Operator-facing Telegram status now also splits cleanly between built-ins and routed work. Queue-backed commands like `/monitor`, `/quota`, `/prd`, and `/tasks` read live runtime state directly instead of relying on conversational summaries, so queue progress, roadmap status, provider health, and actionable worklists stay aligned with the SQLite authority DB. Queue totals use one canonical denominator everywhere: all live executable tasks, excluding only split parents. `/prd` now also distinguishes empty roadmap stages from frozen or decomposed ones: stages with only frozen work are shown as `frozen`, stages with only split parents are shown as `decomposed`, and only truly absent work is shown as `not loaded`. `/monitor` now carries a compact `sdp-cli`-style status slice too: completion-gate status, latest completed run verdict/pair, and per-agent quota/provider health, while still surfacing queue-state drift when the active-task and open-task-run records disagree. `/tasks` now defaults to an operator-first queue view with running work, next root tasks, split-needed work, and attention items, while filtered slices like `/tasks frozen` or `/tasks all 20` expose deeper backlog details on demand. Roadmap-aware task slices such as `/tasks prd 6` and `/tasks stage clone and home creation` resolve through the same roadmap/batch files as `/prd`, so stage-level work inspection stays aligned with the live execution spine.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_daemon_fallback.py:1:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Tests for daemon fallback when agent providers degrade.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_daemon_fallback.py:36:    def get_provider_status(self) -> dict[str, dict[str, object]]:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_daemon_fallback.py:40:        provider = cypherclaw_daemon.PROVIDERS[agent_name]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_daemon_fallback.py:41:        return float(self.status[provider][\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"headroom\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"])\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_daemon_fallback.py:43:    def force_status(self, provider: str, status: str, **_: object) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_daemon_fallback.py:44:        self.status.setdefault(provider, {})\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++tests/test_daemoassert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Restart=on-failure\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in runner_unit\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"ConditionPathExists=/home/user/.local/bin/sdp-cli\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in runner_unit\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Environment=PATH=/home/user/.local/bin:/home/user/cypherclaw/.venv/bin\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in runner_unit\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Environment=PYTHONPATH=/home/user/sdp-cli/src\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in runner_unit\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Restart=always\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in runner_unit\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"RestartPreventExitStatus=75\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in runner_unit\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"SuccessExitStatus=75\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in runner_unit\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n def test_boot_hardening_no_longer_restores_state_or_starts_runner_direc